            <thetext>In the playground example at http://bit.ly/cz47wJ with Console output enabled/visible:

- Single click into any cell repeatedly. In the console you&#39;ll see a message for each click.

- Now double click into any cell in column 0, getting you into edit mode. Leave edit mode (ESC key).

- Now click into the currently focused cell, there will be no console message (the click handler is not
  executed).

  Click into any other cell and there will be only one message in the console, as with the first
  click the cell is focused and focused cells don&#39;t get the click event any longer.

I talked to Alex Steitz on the phone and he can confirm or explain the above in case it&#39;s not clear. Or get back to me, if there is a question.</thetext>
